  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An extensive uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted, including Latin hypercube sampling over 128 design points and Sobol index decomposition to rank input contributions to hemolysis index variance; these UQ activities are documented in the validation report and informed the acceptance decision.",
