    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately not assessed per the MRL 2 requirements table for a Class II device with medium model influence. Discretization error achieved level 3 against a requirement of 2, providing additional confidence. Experimental validation demonstrates mean absolute error of 8.3%, well within the 15% acceptance threshold. The UQ campaign (documented in VR-03) confirms that the model responds appropriately to dominant physical drivers and that the worst-case operating point selection is robust. The credibility assessment team unanimously accepts this model for the stated COU.",
